content.description: Sit start to Gom Jabbar. Start sitting left hand on a sidepull in the center of the roof and right hand on the arete. Pull hard into a compression knee bar (knee pad might be necessary) on right and toe hook at the base of the roof. Climb right into the start of Gom Jabbar and top out the same as Bene Gesserit.
content.location: 50 yards south of the Larry Collins bench there is another gully, walk down hill 50 yards and this large overhanging boulder is the first you will see.

content.description: Start sitting left hand under roof on large sidepull and right hand on a good ledge on the right face. Pull on and and grab some awesome pinches near the arete, continue left along the lip and top out the same as Bene Gesserit.
content.location: 50 yards south of the Larry Collins bench there is another gully, walk down hill 50 yards and this large overhanging boulder is the first you will see.

content.description: Start matched on the very low left jug in the roof. Â With difficulty and trickery, establish and hopefully send. Essentially the problem Gene Besserit with out the giant detached block. Formerly the Toehook Dream Project.
Start matched low under roof on the big side-pulling jug using the detached block underneath for feet, pull a few long moves on good holds and top out up and right over the slab.
